Anno regni Caroli regis Angliæ, Scotiæ, Franciæ, & Hiberniæ, decimo septimo. At the Parliament begun at Westminster the third day of November, Anno Dom. 1640. In the 16 yeer of the reign of our most gracious soveraign Lord, Charles, by the grace of God, of England, Scotland, France, and Ireland King, Defender of the Faith, &c. England and Wales. Parliament.
12 p.
Printed by Robert Barker, Printer to the Kings most excellent Majestie: and by the assignes of John Bill, London : 1641.
Title within ornamental border. Text of acts in black letter; royal arms on frontispiece; initial letter. Contains two acts of Parliament. Reproduction of the original in the Bodleian Library. Act for the better raising and levying of mariners, sailors, and others, for the present guarding of the seas, and necessary defence of the realm, and other his Majesties dominions -- Act for the relief of the captives, taken by Turkish, Moorish, and other pirates, and to prevent the taking of others in time to come.
